<h1><?php echo $header;?></h1>

<p>Personal logs are a great way to get your character(s) involved in character development. Personal logs can be anything from a log (like a diary/journal) entry about what they&rsquo;re thinking or anything else going on in their lives. It&rsquo;s also gives a good opportunity to show a character&rsquo;s history as well. The game master can also choose to use personal logs for other things as well. If you have questions, you should contact your game master about how they think you can best use personal logs.</p>

<p>Personal logs consist of an author, a subject, content, and any tags you want to put on your log for it to be easily found in a search later on. You can post a personal log as your main character or any other character or protected non-playing character associated with your account. All associated character will be in the dropdown menu. If you only have one character, it will just display the character&rsquo;s name.</p>

<p>The email players will receive has the author, the subject and the message. If someone has chosen not to receive email notifications of personal logs and will have to manually look through personal logs the next time they login to Nova.</p>

<h4>Permissions</h4>

<p>In order to write a mission post, a user needs <kbd>write/personallog</kbd> privileges.</p>

<h2>Saving Personal Logs</h2>

<p>Personal logs can be saved so that you can work on them for a little while then come back to it later on. In order to save a personal log, you only need to have an author set and you can click Save. Your saved personal logs will show up in your list of saved entries.</p>

<h2>Deleting Personal Logs</h2>

<p>You can only delete a personal log from the write pages if it&rsquo;s in the saved status. If you decide you don&rsquo;t want to do a personal log that you&rsquo;ve already saved, just click Delete and it will be deleted. After deleting the saved personal log, you will be redirected to the Admin Control Panel after 5 seconds.</p>